PREAMBLE

This is a software license for the Co-Owned Software Model (COSM).

Most open-source licenses protect the freedom to read, modify, and
share code. That is necessary but not sufficient. When software is
operated as a service, the people who depend on it — the users, the
customers, the communities — have no seat at the table. The operator
makes every decision: pricing, privacy, availability, direction. The
source code is technically open, but the power is closed.

COSM addresses this gap. It starts from a strong copyleft foundation:
all source code must remain available, and network use triggers the
same obligations as distribution. Then it adds one further requirement:
if you operate this software as a service for paying users, those
users must have meaningful governance rights over the operation of
that service.

The philosophy is simple. Code should be free. Governance should be
shared. If you profit from other people's dependence on software, those
people deserve a voice in how it is run.

You are free to use, study, modify, and share this software without
restriction. You are free to run it for yourself or within your
organization. The governance requirement activates only when you
operate it as a commercial service for others — and only above a
revenue threshold that keeps small projects unburdened.

This license was created by the destroysaas cooperative, where
businesses and product teams (called "cells") collectively own and
govern shared software infrastructure. COSM is our attempt to encode
that model into a license that anyone can use.

