1. Definitions
----------------------------------------------------------------------

1.1 "This License" means version 1.0 of the Co-Owned Software Model
    License (COSM).

1.2 "The Software" means the source code, object code, documentation,
    and any other material to which the copyright holder has attached a
    notice stating that it is released under This License.

1.3 "You" (or "Your") means an individual or legal entity exercising
    permissions granted by This License. For legal entities, "You"
    includes any entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under
    common control with You. "Control" means ownership of more than
    fifty percent (50%) of the voting power of an entity.

1.4 "Contribution" means any work of authorship submitted to the
    copyright holder for inclusion in The Software, including
    modifications, additions, and new files.

1.5 "Contributor" means any individual or legal entity that creates or
    contributes to a Contribution.

1.6 "Source Code" means the preferred form of the work for making
    modifications to it, including all modules it contains, plus any
    associated interface definition files, scripts used to control
    compilation and installation, and documentation.

1.7 "Modified Version" means any work that contains The Software or
    any portion of it, whether verbatim or with modifications, and/or
    translated into another language or format.

1.8 "Distribute" means to make copies of The Software available to
    third parties, whether by transfer, publication, or any other
    means.

1.9 "Operate as a Service" means to make the functionality of The
    Software or a Modified Version available to third parties over a
    computer network, where those third parties interact with the
    running software remotely, regardless of whether they receive a
    copy of The Software itself.

1.10 "Service Users" means the third parties who use, access, or
     interact with The Software when it is Operated as a Service.

1.11 "Commercial Service" means Operating as a Service where:
     (a) Service Users pay fees, subscriptions, or other charges to
         access or use The Software; or
     (b) the operator derives revenue from The Software's operation
         through advertising, data licensing, or other commercial
         activity directly tied to the service; or
     (c) the operator charges for support, hosting, or managed
         services where The Software provides the primary
         functionality.

1.12 "Revenue Threshold" means one hundred thousand United States
     dollars (USD $100,000) in annual gross revenue derived from a
     Commercial Service. Revenue is measured per legal entity (and its
     controlled affiliates) per calendar year.

1.13 "Cooperative Governance" means a governance structure that
     satisfies the requirements of Section 7.

1.14 "Major Decision" means any decision concerning:
     (a) pricing changes that exceed twenty percent (20%) in any
         twelve-month period;
     (b) changes to the privacy policy or data handling practices;
     (c) discontinuation or material reduction of the service;
     (d) transfer of ownership or control of the service operation;
     (e) changes to the terms of service that materially affect
         Service Users' rights; or
     (f) allocation of surplus revenue beyond operational costs and
         reasonable reserves.

