5. Free Use: No Restrictions
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The following uses of The Software carry no obligations beyond
attribution (Section 4.4) and source availability (Section 4):

(a) Personal use for any purpose.
(b) Internal use within Your organization, even if Your organization
    is a commercial entity, provided the software is not Operated as
    a Service for third parties.
(c) Use for research, education, experimentation, or evaluation.
(d) Use by nonprofit organizations and charitable institutions for
    any purpose, including Operating as a Service, provided no
    individual or entity derives private commercial benefit from the
    operation.
(e) Operating as a Service on a non-commercial basis (no fees
    charged, no revenue derived).

----------------------------------------------------------------------
6. Commercial Service: Governance Threshold
----------------------------------------------------------------------

6.1 If You Operate The Software as a Commercial Service and Your
    annual gross revenue from that Commercial Service exceeds the
    Revenue Threshold, You must establish and maintain Cooperative
    Governance as defined in Section 7 within one hundred eighty
    (180) days of exceeding the threshold.

6.2 If Your annual gross revenue from the Commercial Service is at
    or below the Revenue Threshold, the Cooperative Governance
    requirement does not apply. You must still comply with all other
    terms of This License, including source availability.

6.3 The Revenue Threshold is calculated per distinct Commercial
    Service. Revenue from unrelated products or services does not
    count toward the threshold.

6.4 Once the Cooperative Governance requirement has been triggered,
    it remains in effect for as long as You continue to Operate the
    Commercial Service, even if revenue subsequently falls below the
    Revenue Threshold.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
7. Cooperative Governance Requirements
----------------------------------------------------------------------

When the Cooperative Governance requirement applies under Section 6,
the operator of the Commercial Service must satisfy all of the
following conditions:

7.1 VOTING RIGHTS

    All Service Users who have maintained an active account or
    membership for at least ninety (90) days must have the right to
    vote on Major Decisions. Voting must be conducted by a method
    that is accessible and transparent to all eligible voters.

    Each eligible Service User gets one vote. Voting power may not
    be allocated in proportion to fees paid, data contributed, or
    any other measure of economic activity.

7.2 LIMITS ON CONCENTRATION OF POWER

    No single entity (including its controlled affiliates) may hold
    or exercise more than forty-nine percent (49%) of the total
    voting power on any Major Decision. If a governance structure
    includes multiple classes of voting rights (for example, an
    operator class and a user class), no single class held primarily
    by one entity may constitute a majority.

7.3 FINANCIAL TRANSPARENCY

    The operator must publish, at least annually and in a form
    accessible to all Service Users:
    (a) total revenue derived from the Commercial Service;
    (b) a summary of operating expenses in reasonable categories;
    (c) compensation paid to the five highest-compensated
        individuals or entities involved in operating the service;
    (d) how surplus revenue (revenue exceeding operating expenses
        and reasonable reserves) has been allocated; and
    (e) any material financial relationships between the operator
        and third parties that could create conflicts of interest.

7.4 OPERATIONAL TRANSPARENCY

    The operator must provide Service Users with:
    (a) a public roadmap of planned material changes, updated at
        least quarterly;
    (b) notice of Major Decisions at least thirty (30) days before
        a vote is held; and
    (c) a published process for Service Users to propose items for
        vote.

7.5 RIGHT OF EXIT

    The operator must provide Service Users with:
    (a) the ability to export their data in a standard,
        machine-readable format at any time; and
    (b) at least one hundred eighty (180) days notice before any
        discontinuation of the service.

7.6 GOVERNANCE DOCUMENTATION

    The operator must publish a governance document that describes
    how each of the requirements in this Section 7 is satisfied.
    This document must be accessible to all Service Users and kept
    up to date.

